PN,39402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1776777070
OL,3,COne of the UK's oldest jazz bands play
OL,4,Clast gig after 77 years performing
OL,6,FPeter has has been a member of the
OL,7,Fband since 1980 after he first heard
OL,8,Fthem play at the Cavern Club.
OL,10,F"I was asked would I like to join when
OL,11,Fthe previous trombone player left ...
OL,12,Fit was blooming hard work," he said.
OL,14,FHe was given a stack of tapes to learn
OL,15,Ftheir songs: "They were playing songs
OL,16,Fno one else played."
OL,18,F"You should be able to learn it in a
OL,19,Fcouple of weeks," he was told. "More
OL,20,Flike two years!" Peter joked.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
